# The Goldilocks Zone

Sweet spot training — the magical zone between tempo and threshold where you get maximum adaptation for manageable suffering. Not too easy, not too hard, just right. Two 20-minute blocks at 90% FTP.

- 10:00 45%
  - :30 Warm up easy
  - 5:00 Loosen up the legs, find your pedaling groove
  - 3:00 Sweet spot starts in 2 minutes
  - :30 This will feel hard but doable — that's the point
- 20:00 90%
  - :30 First sweet spot block — settle into the effort
  - 5:00 Breathing is labored but you can still speak in short sentences
  - 5:00 Halfway — stay mentally engaged, focus on form
  - 5:00 5 minutes to go — this is where the adaptation happens
  - 3:00 Almost there — don't let the power drift
  - :30 Done! Nice work
- 5:00 50%
  - :10 Recovery — great first block
  - 3:00 Second block in 2 minutes
  - :30 Same target — you've done this once already
- 20:00 90%
  - :30 Round two — dig in, this one's tougher on tired legs
  - 5:00 That's the point — you're building fatigue resistance
  - 5:00 Halfway through the last block, keep it steady
  - 5:00 Final 5 minutes — you know you can do this
  - 3:00 2 minutes to go — hold the power, hold your form
  - 1:00 Last minute — don't fade, finish strong
- 10:00 40%
  - :10 Done! Excellent sweet spot work today
  - 5:00 Easy spinning to cool down
